Description: Egyptian terracotta figure of a woman. Mould-made from a two-piece mould and solid. Traces of a white coating. Red-brown Nile silt fabric, with abundant mica and sand inclusions. Head only.
Curator's comments: Found unregistered, but with labels from the EEF stating they were from Petrie's excavations at Naukratis in 1885, however objects from Kamiros were also in this box.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DD.388) (Phase 3)
